# Sentence-per-line Markdown

Write each sentence on its own line; no soft line-wrapping within a
sentence.

When editing an existing paragraph, convert only the touched
paragraph to this style; do not reformat surrounding paragraphs that
have not been changed.

Apply to Markdown files, READMEs, docstrings, and inline comments.

## Why

Diffs are cleaner and code review is easier when prose is line-
oriented. This is the same rule minip uses; the convention is
shared across the workspace.
